2

Title

Token not persisted correctly after user login (backend misconfiguration)

Reporter

Sbika Mohamed

Submit Date

16/05/2025

Verifier

 

Summary

After successful login, the backend (NestJS) generates a JWT token but fails to persist it properly due to incorrect response configuration. The token is neither set as a cookie nor returned clearly in the response, which causes session handling issues.

URL

/appointments/get_all

Screenshot

Platform

Backend Plasfora (NestJS)

Operating System

Windows 11

Browser

chrome

Steps to reproduce

Send a POST request with valid credentials to the login route

Backend authenticates user and generates JWT token

Backend responds without setting the token in an appropriate header or cookie

 

Expected result

Backend should persist the token or return it clearly in the response for further usage

Actual result

Token is either omitted from the response, improperly formatted, or not stored due to missing headers or misconfigured response

Severity

Major

Assigned to

Sbika Mohamed

Priority

High

Notes

JWT token is generated but not returned or persisted.
